<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,310,616,642]" box="[189,310,616,642]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,616,642]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,616,642]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,662,794]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Black species with white, connected microtrichiose fasciae on tergites (
<figureCitation box="[1050,1150,662,688]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Megatrigon spp., habitus, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849878/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Figs 1H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1165,1202,663,689]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1862,1888]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Megatrigon spp., abdomen, dorsal view, ♁. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849902/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">7H</figureCitation>
) and bicoloured wing resulting from dense microtrichia, white in proximal 0.6 and brown in distal 0.4 (
<figureCitation box="[1217,1310,697,724]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1494,1520]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,610,1456]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,609,1457]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Megatrigon spp., right wing, ♁. A. Megatrigon apiformis sp. nov. B. M. cooksoni sp. nov. C. M. tabanoides sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849894/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
). Frons shiny; vertex and post-ocular orbit white microtrichiose except area between posterior ocelli, medioposterior part, spots at eye corner and posterior dorsal margin of head (
<figureCitation box="[1021,1100,768,794]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatrigon spp., head, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E–F. M.natalensissp. nov.(arrow =postocellarspot)(♁).G.M.sexmaculatus sp. nov.(♁).H. M.apiformis sp. nov. (♁). I. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). J. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). K. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). L. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). M. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀). Symbol: x = postocellar spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849882/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 2I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,324,834,860]" box="[189,324,834,860]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,834,860]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,834,860]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,880,942]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">The species epithet, which is formed as a male genitive, is derived from the personal name of the collector, Mr. Daniel Montague Cookson.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
