<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,334,1228,1254]" box="[189,334,1228,1254]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,1228,1254]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,1228,1254]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,644,1275,1301]" box="[189,644,1275,1301]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">LENGTH. Body 10.0 mm, wing 7.0 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,1340,1508]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
HEAD (
<figureCitation box="[269,351,1340,1367]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatrigon spp., head, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E–F. M.natalensissp. nov.(arrow =postocellarspot)(♁).G.M.sexmaculatus sp. nov.(♁).H. M.apiformis sp. nov. (♁). I. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). J. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). K. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). L. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). M. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀). Symbol: x = postocellar spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849882/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Figs 2I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[365,404,1340,1366]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[188,231,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Megatrigon spp., left antenna, lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849886/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">3H</figureCitation>
). Distance between eyes, 0.17 × width of head; width of vertical triangle 0.26–0.29 × width of head; postocular orbit wider, the width of postocular orbit dorsally 0.13 × as wide as head; ocellar triangle equilateral, without median longitudinal groove; microtrichia on face well developed and similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[311,467,1446,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochreatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[311,467,1446,1472]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">M. ochreatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[475,611,1446,1472]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: white microtrichiose stripes along eye margin distinct, connected with wide median microtrichiose facial stripe below antennae by narrow oblique stripe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,1546,1678]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">THORAX. Mesoscutum with lateral microtrichiose stripes wide and long, posteriorly connected with scarce prescutellar microtrichia; indistinct submedian stripes ending at conspicuous microtrichiose spots on transverse sutures; traces of median stripe ending near the level of transverse suture; supra-alar setae yellow; mediotergite almost entirely covered by microtrichia.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1066,1717,1744]" box="[189,1066,1717,1744]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
WING (
<figureCitation box="[269,361,1717,1744]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1494,1520]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,610,1456]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,609,1457]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Megatrigon spp., right wing, ♁. A. Megatrigon apiformis sp. nov. B. M. cooksoni sp. nov. C. M. tabanoides sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849894/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
). Setae on costagium white; veins brown; capitulum brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,1783,1845]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">LEGS. Only apex of pro- and mesofemur pale, not the base; tarsi yellow, only tarsomere 1 of metaleg brown dorsally; metatibia dorsally with white microtrichia in proximal half that reach the scar.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,1884,2015]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
ABDOMEN (
<figureCitation box="[319,418,1884,1910]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Megatrigon spp., habitus, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849878/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Figs 1H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[436,476,1884,1910]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1862,1888]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Megatrigon spp., abdomen, dorsal view, ♁. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849902/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">7H</figureCitation>
). Tergites 2–4 black with white transversal microtrichiose fasciae connected medially, on tergites 2+3 touching lateral margins, while on tergite 4 widely separated from them; fasciae on tergites 2+3 oblique and on tergite 4 more straight; tergite 2 with inconspicuous white microtrichia anteromedially, tergite 4 with wide microtrichiose posterior margin. Male genitalia in 
<figureCitation box="[1162,1269,1989,2015]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1825,1851]" captionTargetBox="[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 10. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, epandrium, left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. Megatrigon sp. from sexfasciatus group. M. M. nivalis. Symbols: x = ventral margin of median surstyle; y = posterior surstyle; z = cercus; w = subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849914/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Figs 10H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1280,1331,1989,2015]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium (A–M) and phallus (N), left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. sp. from sexfasciatus group. M–N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = hamus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849918/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">11H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1342,1394,1989,2015]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,232,1794,1820]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 12. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium, ventral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. apiformis sp. nov. G. M. cooksoni sp. nov. H. M. immaculatus sp. nov. I. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. J. M. tabanoides sp. nov. K. Megatrigon sp. from the sexfasciatus group. L. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = lateral ‘shoulders’." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849922/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">12G</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
